From d37f6ceed70ca5833dc776607f4dc77f364ae400 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matheus Sampaio Queiroga <srherobrine20@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 15:11:36 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] pmdomain: airoha: Introduce EN7523 support and direct PLL
 fallback

Extend the airoha-cpu-pmdomain and cpufreq drivers to support the Airoha
EN7523 SoC, alongside the existing AN7581 and AN7583 variants.

Unlike newer variants that rely heavily on ARM Trusted Firmware (ATF) SMC
calls for frequency scaling, the EN7523 integration introduces a fallback
mechanism to directly program the CPU PLL via register writes. This logic
manages the chip-SCU and MCUCFG register spaces to safely switch clocks,
replicating the sequence performed by the BL31 firmware stage.

Accommodate hardware differences by introducing structural SoC match data,
handling the distinct XTAL clock frequencies (20/25 MHz for EN7523 vs 50 MHz
for AN758x), register offsets, and bitmasks.

Additionally, update the airoha-cpufreq driver to manually attach generic
power domains by name and handle their runtime PM lifecycle instead of using
dev_pm_domain_attach_list(), ensuring proper resource management across
all supported SoCs. Update Kconfig and allow/blocklists accordingly.

Signed-off-by: Matheus Sampaio Queiroga <srherobrine20@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/cpufreq/Kconfig.arm                   |   4 +-
 drivers/cpufreq/airoha-cpufreq.c              | 106 +++--
 drivers/cpufreq/cpufreq-dt-platdev.c          |   1 +
 drivers/pmdomain/mediatek/Kconfig             |   5 +-
 .../pmdomain/mediatek/airoha-cpu-pmdomain.c   | 370 +++++++++++++++++-
 5 files changed, 438 insertions(+), 48 deletions(-)

